{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-challenges-generic-show-tsx","path":"/learn/a1-professional-spanish/es-a1-learn-meet-luna/task-5","result":{"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"assignments":[],"bilibiliIds":null,"block":"es-a1-learn-meet-luna","challengeType":19,"description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p>U španskom jeziku mnoge profesije i nacionalnosti imaju rodne oblike. Uobičajeni primeri su:</p>\n<table>\n<thead>\n<tr>\n<th>Taaluma/Utaifa</th>\n<th>Kiume</th>\n<th>Kike</th>\n</tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>Engineer</td>\n<td><span class=\"highlighted-text\">ingeniero</span></td>\n<td><span class=\"highlighted-text\">ingeniera</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Designer</td>\n<td><span class=\"highlighted-text\">diseñador</span></td>\n<td><span class=\"highlighted-text\">diseñadora</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Mexican</td>\n<td><span class=\"highlighted-text\">mexicano</span></td>\n<td><span class=\"highlighted-text\">mexicana</span></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>Puerto Rican</td>\n<td><span class=\"highlighted-text\">puertorriqueño</span></td>\n<td><span class=\"highlighted-text\">puertorriqueña</span></td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>Završetak <span class=\"highlighted-text\">-o</span> je često muški, a <span class=\"highlighted-text\">-a</span> je često ženski.</p>\n<p>Međutim, neke nacionalnosti i profesije koriste istu reč za muškarce i žene. Ne postoji čvrsto pravilo za njihovo prepoznavanje, zato je najbolji način učenja kroz stvarne primere. Na primer:</p>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Soy costarricense.</span> - Mimi ni Mkosta Rika. (isiyo na jinsia)</p>\n<p>Luna anataja utaifa wake kwa Kihispania.</p>\n</section>","nodules":null,"explanation":"<section id=\"explanation\">\n<p>Glagol <span class=\"highlighted-text\">soy</span> dolazi od <span class=\"highlighted-text\">ser</span> i ovde se koristi za opisivanje Lunine nacionalnosti. Na primer:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Soy chilena</span> - Mimi ni Mchile. (wa kike)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Soy mexicana.</span> – Mimi ni Mkemexiko. (wa kike)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Soy colombiano.</span> – Mimi ni Mkolombia. (wa kiume)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Soy puertorriqueño.</span> – Mimi ni Mwenpuetoriko. (wa kiume)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>","helpCategory":"Spanish Curriculum","instructions":"<section id=\"instructions\">\n<p>Slušaj zvuk i odgovori na pitanje ispod.</p>\n</section>","fields":{"slug":"/learn/a1-professional-spanish/es-a1-learn-meet-luna/task-5"},"questions":[{"text":"<p>Utaifa wa Luna ni upi?</p>","answers":[{"answer":"<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Puertorriqueña</span></p>","feedback":"<p>Ovo znači \"Mwenpuetoriko\", ali Luna ovo nije rekla.</p>","audioId":null},{"answer":"<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Mexicana</span></p>","feedback":"<p>Ovo znači \"Mkemexiko\", ali Lunina nacionalnost je drugačija.</p>","audioId":null},{"answer":"<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Colombiana</span></p>","feedback":"<p>Ovo znači \"Mkolombija\", ali Luna je rekla nešto drugo.</p>","audioId":null},{"answer":"<p><span class=\"highlighted-text\">Chilena</span></p>","feedback":null,"audioId":null}],"solution":4}],"scene":{"setup":{"background":"desk.png","characters":[{"character":"Luna","position":{"x":50,"y":25,"z":1.5},"opacity":0}],"audio":{"filename":"ES_A1_spanish_meet_luna.mp3","startTime":1,"startTimestamp":5.63,"finishTimestamp":6.61},"alwaysShowDialogue":null},"commands":[{"background":null,"character":"Luna","position":null,"opacity":1,"startTime":0,"finishTime":null,"dialogue":null},{"background":null,"character":"Luna","position":null,"opacity":null,"startTime":1,"finishTime":1.98,"dialogue":{"text":"Soy chilena.","align":"center"}},{"background":null,"character":"Luna","position":null,"opacity":0,"startTime":2.48,"finishTime":null,"dialogue":null}]},"superBlock":"a1-professional-spanish","tests":[],"title":"Zoe